Michael Vick and three others are facing charges related to a dogfighting conspiracy, with Vick being accused of bankrolling the operation.
Tony Taylor, one of the co-defendants, has pleaded guilty and agreed to cooperate with prosecutors.
The indictment details gruesome acts of animal cruelty, sparking outrage from animal rights groups.
Vick's sponsors have already started cutting ties with him, reflecting the seriousness of the allegations.
This case has drawn comparisons to past scandals in the NFL, highlighting the impact of off-field behavior on players' careers and endorsements.
The legal battle is ongoing, with Vick's future hanging in the balance.
